<item>
            <title>[JDK-8305958] Use links instead of buttons for auto-generated header links</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8305958</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The auto-generated links to headings in JavaDoc-generated documentation implemented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8289332&quot; title=&quot;Auto-generate ids for user-defined headings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8289332&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8289332&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; use buttons to transfer the permalink to the user&amp;#39;s clipboard via JavaScript. After discussing this feature we came to the conclusion the copy-to-clipboard functionality does not add a lot of usefulness compared to just providing plain links to the headings/section. A review of other developer oriented documentation sites reassured us that this is the way to go.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The buttons should be replaced with plain links using a &amp;quot;double chain link&amp;quot; icon as label. Of course usability and accessibility concerns must be considered. &lt;br/&gt;
</description>
